    "created_at": "2023-11-09T13:21:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-11-09T13:21:31Z",
    "body": "`__bp_interactive_mode` is part of https://github.com/rcaloras/bash-preexec/blob/master/bash-preexec.sh and might be installed as part of your terminal emulator (e.g. wezterm installs a [vendored version of it](https://github.com/wez/wezterm/blob/f0e3eecba6faec0aa963a6f0067577afc99e11db/assets/shell-integration/wezterm.sh#L159)). starship seems to recognize that it might exist (https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/master/src/init/starship.bash#L81) but does not seem to need it.\r\n\r\nzsh does not need it that's why using zsh fixed it.\r\n\r\nStarship only works on the server if it is installed and configured on the server: could it be that you have synced some config to the server which assumes bash-preexec installed but the sync didn't install bash-preexec? \r\n\r\nIf you want to track this down, maybe grep your system for any users of it: `grep __bp_interactive_mode ${HOME}` and maybe even `grep __bp_interactive_mode /`\r\n\r\nBut this doesn't look like a bug in starship.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
